#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:3
msgid "Dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:5
msgid ""
"The Dashboard is the first page you will see after you log into OPNsense."
" Additionally, it can be accessed via :menuselection:`Lobby --> "
"Dashboard`. The Dashboard provides an overview of your system status."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:10
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:12
msgid ""
"What is shown on the Dashboard can be configured by adding and removing "
"widgets. Some widgets also allow further configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:15
msgid "By default, the following widgets are present:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:17
msgid ""
"**System Information:**  Shows information about the installation "
"OPNsense version, the hardware in the computer and resource usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:18
msgid ""
"**Services:** Shows running background services and allow starting, "
"stopping and reloading them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:19
msgid "**Gateways:** Shows used gateways."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:20
msgid "**Interfaces:** Shows configured interfaces and their status."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:22
msgid "In the upper right corner of every widget, there are three buttons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:24
msgid ""
"**Edit (pencil icon):** Click this to modify the widget settings. This "
"button is always present, but it can be greyed out if the widget has no "
"configuration options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Minimize (minus icon):** Click this to temporarily collapse this "
"widget. It can be uncollapsed by clicking the 'plus' icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:26
msgid "**Remove (cross icon):** Removes the widget from the Dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:28
msgid "In the upper right corner of the page, there are two or three buttons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:30
msgid ""
"**Add widget:** Opens a dialog window with a list of widgets that can be "
"added to the Dashboard. Simply click on an entry in the list to add it to"
" the Dashboard. Do note that its contents will only show up after you "
"click **Save Settings**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:31
msgid ""
"**1/2/3/4/6 columns:** Changes the amount of columns to show widgets in. "
"By default, this is set to **2**. Do not forget to click **Save "
"Settings** afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/dashboard.rst:32
msgid ""
"**Save Settings:** When you change the amount of columns or collapse a "
"widget, you can make that change persistent by clicking this button. "
"Otherwise the changes will be discarded as soon as you reload the page."
msgstr ""

